                <!--
        <h2>Total Defense</h2>
        <p>Your character concentrates on taking as little damage as possible and takes a defensive stance, either using your weapons to parry incoming attacks, or hiding behind your shield.  When you take this action you cannot move or use Reactions or Bonus Actions, but you gain +4 to AC until the start of your next turn.</p>
        <h2>Charging</h2>
        <p>Charging is a special full-round action that allows you to move up to twice your speed and perform a melee attack in the same round. However, it carries tight restrictions on how you can move.</p>
        <h5>Movement During a Charge</h5>
        <p>You must move before your attack, not after. You must move at least 30 feet directly toward the designated opponent.  You give up any remaining movement after the attack is made.</p>
        <h5>Attacking on a Charge</h5>
        <p>After moving, you may take your melee attack action. You get Advantage to the attack rolls, but take a –2 penalty to your AC until the start of your next turn.<br><br>
        A charging character gets a +5 bonus to Strength checks made to bull rush an opponent (Knock Prone or Knock Back).</p>
        <h5>Lances and Charge Attacks</h5>
        <p>A lance, spear, or trident deals double damage if employed by a mounted character in a charge.</p>
        -->

